for or directed toward commercial advantage or private
monetary compensation.

## Other Rights Reserved

The licensor reserves all rights not granted under this
License, including patent rights, rights in added matter,
and rights to restrict others from doing the same.

## Patent License

The licensor grants you a patent license for the software that
covers patent claims the licensor can license, or becomes able
to license, as a result of agreement to these terms. This
excludes claims that would be infringed only as a consequence
of further modification of the software. If you or your
related entities institute patent litigation or aggressive
patent assertion—that is, litigation or assertion relating to
a patent on an exclusive basis, not as a defense or in a
declaratory judgment action—against anyone for any patent
claim covering the software, your patent license under this
License terminates immediately and completely.

## Noncommercial Purposes

Except under Section 5, you may not do anything with the
software primarily intended for or directed toward commercial
advantage or private monetary compensation, including but not
limited to:

- offering the software for sale
- offering services that depend on or integrate the software
- licensing the software
- leasing the software
- providing the software as part of a larger product
- using the software in a service
- using the software as a hosted service

However, a person or entity can do any of the foregoing if:

- they do so without commercial advantage or private monetary
  compensation, or
- they obtain a separate commercial license from the licensor

## Copyleft

When you distribute the software, you must give recipients
the same rights you received. You must:

- provide a copy of this License, and
- disclose the source of the software with a list of changes
